===Etymology===
[[Medieval Latin]], from {{term|Baioarii|lang=la}} 'Bavarians', from [[Late Latin]] {{term|Bojuvarii|lang=la}}, literally, 'Boii settlers', compound of {{etyl|cel-gau|en}} {{term||Boii}} 'the Boii [[tribe]]' and {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{recons|warjaz|lang=gem-pro}} 'settler' (compare [[Old Norse]] {{term|verjar|lang=non}} 'defender, [[settler]]'), from Proto [[ Indo-European]]
(compare [[Welsh]] {{term|gwerin|lang=cy}} '[[crowd]]', [[Sanskrit]] {{term||vṛndám}} '[[group]], [[troop]], crowd'). This [[name]] was adopted by the [[Marcomanni]] after defeating the Boii and settling [[Bohemia]] and parts of Bavaria.

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|UK}} {{IPA|/bəˈveəɹɪə/}}

===Proper noun===
{{en-proper noun}}

# A [[historical region]] in [[Middle Europe]].
# The [[kingdom]] of Bavaria.
# One of the component states of [[Germany]] according to the current administrative division of the [[nation]], which includes the historical Bavaria and parts of [[Swabia]] and [[Franconia]].

